                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 Stam, John C./64: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-14T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 14, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Your 69, February 9, 10 a.m. and 73, February 13, 11 a.m. Department approves
                    proposed action by the Legation outlined in antepenultimate and penultimate
                    paragraphs of latter telegram.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
